Corona on the continents

Pieter Hobbelen

6/21/2020

On this page we going to look at the Corona data around the world. To do this, we are going to devide the world in regions. The regions are based on the continents and the northern, eastern, southern, western or combinations thereof. Some regions are regions with countries with a specific characteristic, such as islands in an specific ocean. In the table below we see all the regions. We see regions such as North America, where the name says a lot about the coutries in that region. But regions like Mid America, South Africa, etc. are vague. In the table is a column with extra information.

All the regions in the world
Region Continent Extra_information
North America North America Canada and the USA
Mid America North America Main land of Latin America
South America South America Mainland of South America
South Africa Africa African countries below the equator
Mid East Africa Africa Eastern African countries above the equator
North West Africa Africa Western African countries above the equator
North West Europe Europe Western Europe and Scandinavia
East Europe Europe Eastern Europe and Russia
South West Azia Azia Oil states and western Azia
South East Azia Azia Countries located at the coast of the Indian Ocean and Indonesia
Mid Azia Azia Mid Azia except Russia
Oceania Oceania Australia, New Zealand and Paopoea New-Guinea
Pacific and Atlantic Islands Other Small island and archipelagos in the Pacific and the Atlantic

We have now the information the read the figures that we present on this page.
